pytket-honeywell¶

pytket-honeywell is an extension to pytket that allows pytket circuits to be executed on Honeywell’s quantum devices.

pytket-honeywell is available for Python 3.6, 3.7 and 3.8, on Linux and MacOS. To install, run:

pip install pytket-honeywell

pytket.backends.honeywell¶

Backends for processing pytket circuits with Honeywell devices

Interface to a Honeywell device.

Construct a new Honeywell backend.

Parameters

  • api_key (string) – Honeywell API key

  • device_name (string) – device name (suffix of URL, e.g. “HQS-LT-1.0”)

  • label (string) – label to apply to submitted jobs
